WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.386 --> 00:00:55.375
A rectangular section of a wall is painted blue for a mural. Three smaller cans of paint and one larger can appear. The height of the mural is labeled H, and the length is labeled L.

2
00:00:55.400 --> 00:01:17.800
An area model appears. The first part is a smaller rectangle with an area of 3x. The second part is a larger rectangle with the same height and an area of 12. A callout pointing to 3x reads: Each can covers x square meters. A callout pointing to 12 reads: Covers 12 square meters.Then 3 appears along the height of the smaller rectangle and x across its length. Next, 3 appears along the height of the larger rectangle and 4 across its length. So, the height of the area model is 3, and the total length is x plus 4.